  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How should I start losing weight? I study in a hostel have no history of exercise whatsoever. I am 6'2 and 95kg approx.",
  "response": "Starting your weight loss journey while living in a hostel can be challenging but absolutely achievable with the right approach. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide tailored to your situation:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Assess Your Current Habits**\n- Track your daily food intake and activity level using an app like MyFitnessPal or a simple journal.\n- Identify areas for improvement, such as reducing junk food, sugary drinks, or late-night snacks.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Set Realistic Goals**\n- Aim for gradual weight loss (0.5\u20131 kg per week) to ensure it\u2019s sustainable.\n- Focus on building habits rather than quick fixes.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Improve Your Diet**\nSince you\u2019re in a hostel, you may have limited control over meals, but you can still make smart choices:\n- **Prioritize Protein:** Include eggs, chicken, lentils, or beans in your meals to stay full longer.\n- **Choose Whole Foods:** Opt for whole grains (brown rice, whole wheat bread) over processed carbs (white bread, noodles).\n- **Eat More Veggies:** Add vegetables to every meal for fiber and nutrients.\n- **Control Portions:** Use smaller plates or bowls to avoid overeating.\n- **Limit Junk Food:** Avoid sugary snacks, fried foods, and packaged snacks as much as possible.\n- **Stay Hydrated:** Drink plenty of water throughout the day to curb hunger and avoid mistaking thirst for hunger.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Incorporate Movement**\nStart with small, manageable steps to build an active lifestyle:\n- **Walk More:** Aim for 8,000\u201310,000 steps daily. Use stairs instead of elevators and take short walks in your free time.\n- **Bodyweight Exercises:** Begin with basics like push-ups, squats, lunges, and planks. You can do these in your room without equipment.\n- **Hostel-Friendly Workouts:** Look for beginner-friendly bodyweight workout videos on YouTube (e.g., Yoga, Pilates, or HIIT).\n- **Stretch Daily:** Improve flexibility and reduce stress with 10\u201315 minutes of stretching.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Manage Stress and Sleep**\n- **Sleep:** Aim for 7\u20138 hours of quality sleep per night. Poor sleep can disrupt hunger hormones and lead to weight gain.\n- **Stress:** Practice mindfulness, meditation, or deep breathing to manage stress, which can trigger emotional eating.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Stay Consistent and Patient**\n- Focus on progress, not perfection. Small, consistent changes lead to long-term results.\n- Celebrate non-scale victories, like feeling more energetic or fitting into clothes better.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Track Your Progress**\n- Weigh yourself weekly (same time, same day) to monitor progress.\n- Take progress photos or measurements to see changes over time.\n\n---\n\n### **Sample Daily Plan for Hostel Environment**\n**Morning:**\n- Start with a glass of water.\n- Have a balanced breakfast (e.g., eggs, whole wheat toast, and a fruit).\n\n**Afternoon:**\n- Choose a balanced lunch (e.g., rice, dal, vegetables, and lean protein).\n- Take a 10\u201315 minute walk after meals.\n\n**Evening:**\n- Snack on a fruit, nuts, or yogurt instead of chips or sweets.\n- Do a 15\u201320 minute bodyweight workout in your room.\n\n**Night:**\n- Have a light dinner (e.g., whole wheat roti, veggies, and a small portion of protein).\n- Avoid late-night snacks or sugary drinks.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n- Involve friends or roommates to stay motivated.\n- Use free resources like YouTube or apps for workout ideas.\n- Avoid extreme diets\u2014focus on balanced, sustainable changes.\n\n---\n\nBy making small, consistent changes to your diet, activity level, and lifestyle, you\u2019ll start seeing progress over time. Stay patient and committed\u2014you\u2019ve got this! \ud83d\udcaa",
  "temperature": 1.0,
